table.body:
Private schools (also known as 'independent schools') charge fees to attend. They don't get any money from the government. Pupils don't have to follow the [national curriculum.](# "National curriculum")

All private schools must be registered with the government. You can read the [reports of regular inspections.](http://www.isi.net/reports/ "Independent Schools Inspectorate reports"){:rel="external"}

There are also [schools which specialise](http://www.isc.co.uk/ParentZone_SENaccreditedschools.htm "Independent Schools Council list of Special Educational Needs accredited schools"){:rel="external"} in teaching children with special educational needs.
